const stateFull = 'Illinois';
const slug = 'chicago-il';
const county = 'Cook County';
const fireDept = 'Chicago Fire Department';
---
<Base title={`Fire Safety Services in ${city}, ${state} — Inspection, Installation & Compliance`} description={`Fire safety services for Chicago, IL commercial properties. Fire extinguisher inspection, fire alarm installation, sprinkler systems, kitchen suppression, and Chicago Fire Prevention Code compliance. Chicago Fire Department violation remediation and pre-inspection consulting.`} canonical={`https://firesafetysupplyhouse.com/fire-safety-services-chicago-il/`}>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-gray-50 to-white py-16"><div class="section">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-gray-400 mb-8"><a href="/" class="hover:text-gray-700 no-underline">Home</a><span>/</span><span class="text-gray-700">Fire Safety Services in {city}, {state}</span></nav>
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-red-brand mb-3">Serving Chicago, Illinois — Cook County</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-5 leading-tight">Fire Safety Services in Chicago, IL</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-6">Complete fire protection services for commercial properties in Chicago, Illinois. Fire extinguisher inspection, fire alarm installation, sprinkler systems, kitchen suppression, and Chicago Fire Prevention Code compliance consulting — performed by licensed professionals to keep your building compliant with Chicago Fire Department requirements and NFPA standards.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3"><button onclick={`openRFQ('','','Fire Safety Services - ${city}, ${state}')`} class="btn-primary text-sm">Schedule a Fire Safety Inspection</button><a href="mailto:quotes@firesafetysupplyhouse.com" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 hover:border-gray-400 transition-colors no-underline">Contact Us</a></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>
  <section class="bg-red-brand text-white py-4"><div class="section text-center"><p class="text-sm font-medium">⚠️ Don't wait for a violation. Chicago Fire Prevention Code violations carry escalating daily fines and potential occupancy restrictions. Chicago Fire Department is one of the nation's most active enforcement agencies.</p></div></section>
  <section class="py-16"><div class="section">
    <div class="text-center mb-12"><h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3">Fire Protection Services for Chicago Businesses</h2><p class="text-base text-gray-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">We provide every fire safety service your Chicago commercial property needs to stay compliant with Chicago Fire Department requirements and NFPA standards.</p></div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="card p-6 flex flex-col"><div class="text-3xl mb-3">🧯</div><h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Fire Extinguisher Inspection &amp; Service</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-1 mb-3">NFPA 10 compliant fire extinguisher inspections for Chicago commercial properties. Monthly visual checks, annual professional inspections, 6-year internal examinations, and 12-year hydrostatic testing. All service by licensed fire protection technicians.</p><div class="flex items-center justify-between"><span class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand bg-red-light px-2 py-1 rounded">NFPA 10</span><button onclick={`openRFQ('','','Fire Extinguisher Service - ${city}, ${state}')`} class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand hover:underline bg-transparent border-0 cursor-pointer">Get Quote →</button></div></div>
      <div class="card p-6 flex flex-col"><div class="text-3xl mb-3">🔔</div><h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Fire Alarm System Installation &amp; Testing</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-1 mb-3">Complete fire alarm system design, installation, and annual testing for Chicago commercial buildings. Addressable and conventional systems, smoke detectors, pull stations, horn/strobes, and monitoring. Full compliance with NFPA 72 and Chicago Fire Department requirements.</p><div class="flex items-center justify-between"><span class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand bg-red-light px-2 py-1 rounded">NFPA 72</span><button onclick={`openRFQ('','','Fire Alarm Installation - ${city}, ${state}')`} class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand hover:underline bg-transparent border-0 cursor-pointer">Get Quote →</button></div></div>
      <div class="card p-6 flex flex-col"><div class="text-3xl mb-3">💧</div><h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Fire Sprinkler System Installation &amp; Inspection</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-1 mb-3">Fire sprinkler design, installation, and inspection for Chicago commercial properties. Wet, dry, pre-action, and deluge systems. Quarterly, semi-annual, and five-year inspections per NFPA 25. Chicago enforces its own Fire Prevention Code — not the IFC. Fire protection contractors must hold Chicago city certification in addition to Illinois state licensing.</p><div class="flex items-center justify-between"><span class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand bg-red-light px-2 py-1 rounded">NFPA 13 / NFPA 25</span><button onclick={`openRFQ('','','Fire Sprinkler Inspection - ${city}, ${state}')`} class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand hover:underline bg-transparent border-0 cursor-pointer">Get Quote →</button></div></div>
      <div class="card p-6 flex flex-col"><div class="text-3xl mb-3">🍳</div><h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Commercial Kitchen Fire Suppression</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-1 mb-3">Wet chemical fire suppression for Chicago restaurants and food service operations. Design, installation, semi-annual inspection, and recharge. Ansul, Amerex, and Kidde certified. Required for all commercial cooking per NFPA 96.</p><div class="flex items-center justify-between"><span class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand bg-red-light px-2 py-1 rounded">NFPA 96</span><button onclick={`openRFQ('','','Kitchen Suppression - ${city}, ${state}')`} class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand hover:underline bg-transparent border-0 cursor-pointer">Get Quote →</button></div></div>
      <div class="card p-6 flex flex-col"><div class="text-3xl mb-3">📋</div><h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Fire Code Compliance Consulting</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-1 mb-3">Fire code compliance audits, violation remediation, and pre-inspection consulting for Chicago commercial properties. We help property managers resolve Chicago Fire Department violations and prepare for inspections under the Chicago Fire Prevention Code.</p><div class="flex items-center justify-between"><span class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand bg-red-light px-2 py-1 rounded">NFPA 101</span><button onclick={`openRFQ('','','Fire Code Compliance - ${city}, ${state}')`} class="text-xs font-bold text-red-brand hover:underline bg-transparent border-0 cursor-pointer">Get Quote →</button></div></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>
  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16"><div class="section"><div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Chicago Fire Code Requirements</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The City of Chicago enforces its own Chicago Fire Prevention Code — not the International Fire Code (IFC) used by most US cities — through the Chicago Fire Department Bureau of Fire Prevention. Chicago's fire code is a distinct municipal ordinance with unique requirements that differ significantly from the IFC in areas including inspection frequency, alarm system design, suppression system specifications, and enforcement procedures. This makes Chicago fire code compliance materially different from compliance in other major US cities. All fire protection work in Chicago must be performed by contractors licensed by the City of Chicago — a separate license from the Illinois State Fire Marshal license.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Chicago's commercial landscape spans the Loop's iconic high-rise office and hotel corridor, River North's dense restaurant and nightlife district, the McCormick Place convention complex (largest in North America), Wrigleyville and Boystown entertainment zones, the Fulton Market innovation district, and extensive industrial and warehouse operations on the South and West Sides. Chicago's cold winters — with temperatures regularly below 0°F with wind chill — create fire protection system challenges including frozen wet pipe sprinklers, heating equipment fires, and cold-weather degradation of alarm system batteries.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Key standards include <a href="/compliance/nfpa-10/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 10</a>, <a href="/compliance/nfpa-72/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 72</a>, and <a href="/compliance/nfpa-25/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 25</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">Chicago Fire Prevention Contacts</h3>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <div><p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-800">Chicago Fire Department — Fire Prevention</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">10 W. 35th Street, Chicago, IL 60616</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Phone: (312) 747-6696</p></div>
          <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-3"><p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-800">Illinois State Fire Marshal</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Licensing & Enforcement: (217) 785-0969</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">Inspection Frequency Requirements</h3>
