    </div>
  </div></div></section>
  <section class="py-16"><div class="section">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-center">Commercial Properties We Serve in Chicago</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4"><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">High-Rise Office & Hotels</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Restaurants & River North</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Convention & Event Centers</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Retail & Michigan Avenue</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Warehouses & Industrial</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Multi-Family Residential</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Healthcare & Medical</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Universities & Education</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Entertainment Venues</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Historic Buildings</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Houses of Worship</span></div><div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Manufacturing Facilities</span></div></div>
  </div></section>
  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16"><div class="section max-w-3xl">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What fire safety services are required for commercial buildings in Chicago, IL?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Chicago enforces the Chicago Fire Prevention Code (unique — not IFC). Requirements include fire extinguishers (NFPA 10), fire alarms (NFPA 72), sprinklers (NFPA 13/25), and kitchen suppression for commercial cooking (NFPA 96). Chicago enforces its own Fire Prevention Code — not the IFC. Fire protection contractors must hold Chicago city certification in addition to Illinois state licensing.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often are fire inspections required in Chicago?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The Chicago Fire Department conducts annual commercial property inspections. Fire extinguishers: monthly visual checks and annual professional inspection. Fire alarms: annual testing. Sprinklers: quarterly, semi-annual, and annual inspections. Kitchen suppression: semi-annual per NFPA 96.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What makes Chicago's fire code different from other cities?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Chicago enforces its own Chicago Fire Prevention Code — a distinct municipal ordinance that is not the IFC. Key differences include: Chicago-specific inspection intervals that may differ from IFC schedules, Chicago Fire Department certification requirements for fire protection contractors (separate from Illinois State Fire Marshal licensing), unique high-rise fire protection requirements reflecting Chicago's architectural legacy, and specific requirements for the Loop's mixed-use high-rise buildings. If your fire protection contractor is licensed only by the Illinois State Fire Marshal and not by the City of Chicago, they cannot legally perform fire protection work in Chicago proper.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Do restaurants in Chicago need special fire suppression systems?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes. All commercial cooking producing grease-laden vapors requires a wet chemical suppression system per NFPA 96, plus a Class K extinguisher within 30 feet of cooking equipment. Systems must be inspected semi-annually by a licensed technician.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who enforces fire codes in Chicago, IL?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The Chicago Fire Department enforces fire codes within Chicago limits. The Illinois State Fire Marshal licenses fire protection contractors at (217) 785-0969.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>
